I",<p>Cablegram, Wellington, 20 March 1951</p>

<p>37. IMMEDIATE TOP SECRET</p>

<p>Thank you for your personal message[1] on the Pacific Pact. I entirely share the views you express. We have greatly welcomed the opportunity of discussing the whole matter with Mr. Watt, who is taking back with him the draft communication which I would like to send to Mr. Attlee.[2]</p>

<p>We would be grateful for any comments and views you may care to express.</p>

<p>_1 Document 63.</p>

<p>2 See Document 68.</p>

<p>_</p>

<p><em>[NAA : A6768, EATS 77, iii]</em></p>
:ET